<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1845. In the general collection at the NHRS we found more similar specimens under the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom&quot; with the same labels: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Rhodus”">&quot;Rhodus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Hedenborg”">&quot;Hedenborg&quot;</normalizedToken>
. They belong to different species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" refId="B19" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1845. Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Berlingianis, Lund, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.66977" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." url="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" year="1845">Dahlbom (1845</bibRefCitation>
: 4) wrote: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nob. ♂ Rhodus rar. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Hedenborg</emphasis>
&quot;. It is not possible to know how many specimens he examined, but we guess few specimens (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">rar.</emphasis>
), as written in the introduction. Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 53) wrote: &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">Duo specimina ex Insula Rhodo vidi, unum a D. Hedenborg alterum a D. Loew lecta</emphasis>
.&quot; The second specimen is not a type, because the material collected by Loew was not included in the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="32" pageNumber="111">
The history of the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">
<pageBreakToken pageId="33" pageNumber="112" start="start">Holopyga</pageBreakToken>
amoenula
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather confused, since it was used by many authors to identify almost all the European species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The synthesis of this confused situation can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B37" refString="Kimsey, LS, Bohart, RM, 1991 1990. The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991</bibRefCitation>
: 225), where many species belonging to different species groups are placed in synonym with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Monografie del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Saint-Pierre, Aosta" pageId="47" pageNumber="126" refId="B77" refString="Rosa, P, 2006. I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta. Monografie del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Saint-Pierre, Aosta" title="I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta." year="2006">Rosa 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 136). More generally, the most common European species, currently known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga generosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="generosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga generosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1853) (= 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="ovata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854) is found in synonym with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry’s">Mocsary's</normalizedToken>
monograph (
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A" journalOrPublisher="Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" refId="B62" refString="Mocsary, A, 1889. Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi. Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" title="Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi." year="1889">1889</bibRefCitation>
: 127). The same taxonomical overview was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mingo, E" journalOrPublisher="HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" refId="B56" refString="Mingo, E, 1994. . HymenopteraChrysididae. Fauna Iberica Vol. 6" volume="Vol. 6" year="1994">Mingo (1994</bibRefCitation>
: 73, 204) whereas in the other most important monographs (i.e. 
<bibRefCitation author="Trautmann, W" journalOrPublisher="Uschman, Weimar" pageId="48" pageNumber="127" refId="B101" refString="Trautmann, W, 1927. Die Goldwespen Europas. Uschman, Weimar" title="Die Goldwespen Europas." year="1927">Trautmann 1927</bibRefCitation>
: 50, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Berland, L" journalOrPublisher="Faune de France" pageId="43" pageNumber="122" refId="B6" refString="Berland, L, Bernard, F, 1938. Hymenopteres Vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae [sic], Trigonalidae). Faune de France vol. 34" title="Hymenopteres Vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae [sic], Trigonalidae)." volume="vol. 34" year="1938">Berland and Bernard 1938</bibRefCitation>
: 42), 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered as variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga gloriosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga gloriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="gloriosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">gloriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius has been suppressed by the ICZN Commission (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" pagination="194 - 196" refId="B34" refString="ICZN, 1998. Opinion 1906: Euchroeus Latreille, 1809 (Insecta, Hymenoptera): conserved; Chrysis purpurata Fabricius, 1787 (currently Euchroeus purpuratus): specific name conserved; and Chrysis gloriosa Fabricius, 1793: specific name supressed. Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature 55 (3): 194 - 196" title="Opinion 1906: Euchroeus Latreille, 1809 (Insecta, Hymenoptera): conserved; Chrysis purpurata Fabricius, 1787 (currently Euchroeus purpuratus): specific name conserved; and Chrysis gloriosa Fabricius, 1793: specific name supressed." volume="55" year="1998">ICZN 1998</bibRefCitation>
, Opinion 1906) and the species previously identified with this name 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">sensu</emphasis>
Linsenmaier are related with a different species-group, which includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier" baseAuthorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga lucida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lepeletier), 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga inflammata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflammata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga inflammata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga caucasica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, etc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="112">
Only after 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linsenmaier’s">Linsenmaier's</normalizedToken>
revision (
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 232" refId="B45" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">1959</bibRefCitation>
) of the European species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">Holopyga amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was correctly identified and recognized as a distinct, valid species endemic to Rhodes. The discussion on the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="amoenula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="112">amoenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originates in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dahlbom’s">Dahlbom's</normalizedToken>
monograph (
